{"questionId":"31992071","questionHtml":"<p>Describe fully these transformations, including the order in which they occur.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>vertical stretch scale factor <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> The vertical stretch can occur in any order.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong><br>translation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>3</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math> followed by horizontal stretch scale factor <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong><br>horizontal stretch scale factor <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math> followed by translation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1A0</strong></em> in either approach, for correct transformations, but incorrect order.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"31992071","referenceCode":"24N.1.AHL.TZ0.10a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Describe fully these transformations, including the order in which they occur.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.8—Transformations of graphs, composite transformations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}